      <hedline>
        <hl1>Let's Show Off Our Beets</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Marc-Paul Bloome letter on Marian Burros's May 31 article notes beets are sold cooked, not raw, in French food stalls; lauds way Mexicans display vegetables in even low-end street markets</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Regarding Marian Burros's article ''Who Put the Beet in the Mousseline?'' (May 31): I lived in France. Beets there, in the food stalls in the various street markets, are sold cooked, not raw.</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Regarding Marian Burros's article ''Who Put the Beet in the Mousseline?'' (May 31): I lived in France. Beets there, in the food stalls in the various street markets, are sold cooked, not raw.</p>
        <p>I also lived in Mexico City. The vegetable displays in the low-end street markets, in cleanliness and look, make the displays at our supermarkets (and farmers' markets, too) seem shameful. The Mexican vendors take pride in displaying their produce. Would it take too much to ask them to bring their craft here and show us how vegetables should be displayed and handled?</p>
        <p>MARC -PAUL BLOOME  New York</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
